cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with statistical inference in graphs with pairwise measurements and side information, which is a problem that falls under the intersection of several subfields in computer science. The use of statistical learning theory and the focus on sample complexity suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely categories. The use of tree decompositions and the analysis of sparse graphs suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the consideration of side information suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
